{{Infobox battle item |name = Protein |image = [[File:Protein_Item.png]] |caption = In-Game image of the ''Protein''. |price = As per the table below |location = [[shops#Kanto: Locations and items|Indigo Plateau Kanto]], [[shops#Johto: Locations and items|Indigo Plateau Johto]], [[shops#Hoenn: Locations and items|Pokémon League Hoenn]], [[Battle Frontier]], [[shops#Sinnoh: Locations and items|Hearthome City]], [[shops#Sinnoh: Locations and items|Pokémon League Sinnoh]] }}
'''Protein''' is a consumable item which can be purchased from each [[Regions|Region's]] League, or traded for [[Berries]] with the [[Berry Master]] of each region from [[Johto]] onwards. It can be fed to a Pokémon to increase the amount of attack that Pokémon gains by 1 per protein per hatch. Each Pokémon can consume a total of 5 proteins per unlocked region.
==How to Use== Go to Start Menu > Items > Item Bag, select the protein and select a Pokémon to use it on. Once used, the effect is permanent and cannot be removed by any means.
==New Efficiency== Below is a list of the most efficient Pokémon to breed after they have been fed the max amount of proteins for that region unlock. The first table for each region ignores non-native damage reduction and event Pokémon. The second (collapsed) table takes those into account and is suggested for use at the beginning of a new region. Breeding efficiency is determined by the following formula:
<math>\text{Egg Cycles} = \frac{\text{Egg Steps}}{40}</math>
<math>\text{Breeding Efficiency} = \frac{0.25 \times \text{Base Attack} + \text{Proteins Used}}{\text{Egg Cycles}} </math>
